<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>PreMedTalk</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0-beta3/css/all.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/header.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/front.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/articles.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/newsletter.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/authors.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/footer.css">
</head>
<body>
<div class="page-container">
    <section class="front-section">
        <div class="front">
            <div class="front__text">
                <h1 class="front__heading">PreMedTalk</h1>
                <p class="front__body">A PreMed Blog</p>
                <p class="front__description">
                    Welcome to PreMedTalk, a McMaster student-led initiative. Our weekly articles and mailing list cover a
                    range of topics including medicine, medical schools, health, and global healthcare news, all aimed at
                    making medical school information accessible to pre-med and undergraduate students. Explore our blog
                    and discover a new way to experience health and wellness.
                </p>
                <p class="front__description">
                    OUR MISSION<br>
                    At PreMedTalk, we are dedicated to demystifying the journey to becoming a medical professional. As
                    aspiring healthcare providers ourselves, we understand the challenges and complexities faced by pre-med
                    students. Our mission is to provide accessible, reliable, and comprehensive information that empowers
                    future medical students.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="front__image-container">
                <img src="/img/placeholder-index-image.avif" alt="intro" class="main-image">
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
<div class="articles-wrapper">
        <section class="articles">
            <h2 class="article__heading">Latest Articles</h2>
            <div class="article-grid">
                <% data.slice(0, 3).forEach(post => { %>
                    <a href="/post/<%= post._id %>" class="article-card">
                        <img src="<%= post.imageUrl %>" alt="<%= post.title %>" class="article-thumbnail">
                        <div class="article-info">
                            <h3><%= post.title %></h3>
                            <p><%- post.body.substring(0, 100) %>...</p>
                            <div class="article-details">
                                <span class="article-view-count">Views: <%= post.viewCount %></span>
                                <span class="article-like-count">â™¥</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </a>
                <% }) %>            
            </div>
        </div>
        </section>    

        <div class="newsletter-subscription-wrapper">
        <section class="newsletter-subscription">
            <h2>Subscribe to Our Newsletter!</h2>
            <form action="/subscribe" method="POST">
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label for="subscribeEmail" class="email-label">Enter your email here *</label>
                    <input type="email" id="subscribeEmail" name="email" placeholder=" " required>
                    <button type="submit">Sign Up</button>
                </div>
                <p class="submission-message">Thanks for submitting!</p>
            </form>
        </section>
        </div>

        <div class="authors-section-wrapper">
        <section class="authors-section">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Meet the Authors</h2>
                <div class="underline"></div>
                <p class="authors-description">
                    Welcome to our blog! We are passionate about making pre-med knowledge more accessible and understandable.
                    As second-year Health Sciences students at McMaster University, we are thrilled to share insights, updates,
                    and resources to help aspiring medical professionals on their journey. Get to know us better and see what
                    drives our dedication to healthcare and education!
                </p>
                <div class="authors-container">
                    <div class="author-card-wrapper">
                    <div class="author-card">
                        <img src="/img/ilias.jpg" alt="Ilias" class="author-photo">
                        <h3>Ilias Farooq</h3>
                        <p>Ilias is a second-year Health Sciences student at McMaster University with a focus on family
                            medicine. He is involved in clinical work at Credit Valley Hospital and other clinics and enjoys
                            the dynamics of working with a diverse patient base. He is passionate about advancing his medical
                            knowledge and sharing it with others to improve healthcare accessibility.</p>
                        <div class="social-links">
                            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/iliasff/" class="btn-social">
                                <i class="fab fa-linkedin"></i>
                            </a>
                            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nikostratopoulos" class="btn-social">
                                <i class="fas fa-envelope"></i>
                            </a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="author-card-wrapper">
                    <div class="author-card">
                        <img src="/img/niko.jpg" alt="Niko" class="author-photo">
                        <h3>Niko Stratopoulos</h3>
                        <p>Niko, a fellow second-year at McMaster, combines his roles as a lifeguard and a budding family
                            medicine enthusiast with a deep fascination for human anatomy. His commitment to healthcare is
                            matched by his dedication to community service and his proactive approach to learning and sharing
                            medical knowledge.</p>
                        <div class="social-links">
                            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nikostratopoulos" class="btn-social">
                                <i class="fab fa-linkedin"></i>
                            </a>
                            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nikostratopoulos" class="btn-social">
                                <i class="fas fa-envelope"></i>
                            </a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>